      <h2 class="teal">What does this mean to me?</h2>

      <p><span>If you&rsquo;re still unsure where you stand on crime issues, ask yourself the following questions:</span></p>
      <ul class="c12 lst-kix_lykpz230dq2t-0 start">
            <li>Have you ever been to jail or arrested?&nbsp;If so, how were you treated in those situations by the authority figures? Do you feel that you were treated fairly? Do you feel that the authorities handled the situation in an appropriate way?</li>
            <li>Do you know anyone who is currently in jail or prison?&nbsp;If so, have they ever told you how they are being treated? How do you think prisoners should be treated? Should they have opportunities to better themselves while they are in prison, or should the experience be as miserable as possible for them?</li>
            <li>Is there anything that you do now that you feel should not be against the law? </li>
            <li>If you do break a law, should the punishment that you receive be the same as another person who is different from you but committed the same crime?</li>
      </ul><br>
      
